{
    "publish_date": "2013-05-03T18:29:46.000Z", 
    "score": 0.0013425656355119738, 
    "video_length": "PT5M17S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Is it possible to create something out of nothing?", 
            "dur": "3.563", 
            "start": "15.689"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or, more precisely, can energy be made into matter?", 
            "dur": "3.628", 
            "start": "19.252"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Yes, but only when it comes together", 
            "dur": "1.902", 
            "start": "22.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with its twin, antimatter.", 
            "dur": "2.82", 
            "start": "24.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And there&#39;s something pretty mysterious about antimatter:", 
            "dur": "3.414", 
            "start": "27.602"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there&#39;s way less of it out there than there should be.", 
            "dur": "4.043", 
            "start": "31.016"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s start with the most famous physics formula ever:", 
            "dur": "3.057", 
            "start": "35.059"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "E equals m c squared.", 
            "dur": "2.321", 
            "start": "38.116"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It basically says that mass is concentrated energy,", 
            "dur": "3.295", 
            "start": "40.437"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and mass and energy are exchangeable,", 
            "dur": "2.998", 
            "start": "43.732"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like two currencies with a huge exchange rate.", 
            "dur": "3.413", 
            "start": "46.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "90 trillion Joules of energy", 
            "dur": "1.521", 
            "start": "50.143"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are equivalent to 1 gram of mass.", 
            "dur": "2.457", 
            "start": "51.664"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But how do I actually transform energy into matter?", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "54.121"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The magic word is &lt;i&gt;energy density&lt;/i&gt;.", 
            "dur": "3.345", 
            "start": "57.791"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you concentrate a huge amount", 
            "dur": "2.367", 
            "start": "61.136"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of energy in a tiny space,", 
            "dur": "2.045", 
            "start": "63.503"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "new particles will come into existence.", 
            "dur": "3.331", 
            "start": "65.548"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If we look closer,", 
            "dur": "0.957", 
            "start": "68.879"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we see that these particles always come in pairs,", 
            "dur": "3.362", 
            "start": "69.836"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like twins.", 
            "dur": "1.316", 
            "start": "73.198"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s because particles always have a counterpart,", 
            "dur": "3.13", 
            "start": "74.514"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an antiparticle,", 
            "dur": "1.471", 
            "start": "77.644"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and these are always produced", 
            "dur": "1.783", 
            "start": "79.115"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in exactly equal amounts: 50/50.", 
            "dur": "3.255", 
            "start": "80.898"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This might sound like science fiction,", 
            "dur": "1.708", 
            "start": "84.153"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it&#39;s the daily life of particle accelerators.", 
            "dur": "3.504", 
            "start": "85.861"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the collisions between two protons", 
            "dur": "2.419", 
            "start": "89.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at CERN&#39;s Large Hadron Collider,", 
            "dur": "2.251", 
            "start": "91.784"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "billions of particles and antiparticles", 
            "dur": "2.212", 
            "start": "94.035"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are produced every second.", 
            "dur": "2.002", 
            "start": "96.247"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Consider, for example, the electron.", 
            "dur": "2.499", 
            "start": "98.249"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It has a very small mass and negative electric charge.", 
            "dur": "3.744", 
            "start": "100.748"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s antiparticle, the positron,", 
            "dur": "2.106", 
            "start": "104.492"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "has exactly the same mass,", 
            "dur": "1.785", 
            "start": "106.598"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but a positive electric charge.", 
            "dur": "2.854", 
            "start": "108.383"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, apart from the opposite charges,", 
            "dur": "2.235", 
            "start": "111.237"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "both particles are identical and perfectly stable.", 
            "dur": "3.385", 
            "start": "113.472"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the same is true for their heavy cousins,", 
            "dur": "2.373", 
            "start": "116.857"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the proton and the antiproton.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "119.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Therefore, scientists are convinced", 
            "dur": "2.146", 
            "start": "121.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that a world made of antimatter", 
            "dur": "1.603", 
            "start": "123.366"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would look, feel, and smell just like our world.", 
            "dur": "4.363", 
            "start": "124.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In this antiworld,", 
            "dur": "1.805", 
            "start": "129.332"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we may find antiwater,", 
            "dur": "2.281", 
            "start": "131.137"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "antigold,", 
            "dur": "1.252", 
            "start": "133.418"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and, for example,", 
            "dur": "1.707", 
            "start": "134.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an antimarble.", 
            "dur": "1.498", 
            "start": "136.377"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now imagine that a marble and an antimarble", 
            "dur": "2.007", 
            "start": "137.875"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are brought together.", 
            "dur": "1.502", 
            "start": "139.882"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These two apparently solid objects", 
            "dur": "2.016", 
            "start": "141.384"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would completely disappear", 
            "dur": "1.821", 
            "start": "143.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into a big flash of energy,", 
            "dur": "1.712", 
            "start": "145.221"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "equivalent to an atomic bomb.", 
            "dur": "2.539", 
            "start": "146.933"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because combining matter and antimatter", 
            "dur": "2.337", 
            "start": "149.472"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would create so much energy,", 
            "dur": "1.838", 
            "start": "151.809"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "science fiction is full of ideas", 
            "dur": "1.955", 
            "start": "153.647"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about harnessing the energy stored in antimatter,", 
            "dur": "3.007", 
            "start": "155.602"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for example, to fuel spaceships like Star Trek.", 
            "dur": "2.965", 
            "start": "158.609"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After all, the energy content of antimatter", 
            "dur": "2.86", 
            "start": "161.574"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is a billion times higher than conventional fuel.", 
            "dur": "3.143", 
            "start": "164.434"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The energy of one gram of antimatter would be enough", 
            "dur": "2.318", 
            "start": "167.577"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for driving a car 1,000 times around the Earth,", 
            "dur": "3.35", 
            "start": "169.895"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or to bring the space shuttle into orbit.", 
            "dur": "3.328", 
            "start": "173.245"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So why don&#39;t we use antimatter for energy production?", 
            "dur": "4.301", 
            "start": "176.573"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, antimatter isn&#39;t just sitting around,", 
            "dur": "3.235", 
            "start": "180.874"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "ready for us to harvest.", 
            "dur": "2.151", 
            "start": "184.109"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We have to make antimatter", 
            "dur": "1.509", 
            "start": "186.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "before we can combust antimatter,", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "187.769"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and it takes a billion times more energy", 
            "dur": "2.502", 
            "start": "190.349"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to make antimatter", 
            "dur": "1.523", 
            "start": "192.851"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than you get back.", 
            "dur": "2.237", 
            "start": "194.374"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, what if there was some antimatter in outer space", 
            "dur": "3.181", 
            "start": "196.611"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we could dig it out one day", 
            "dur": "2.105", 
            "start": "199.792"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from an antiplanet somewhere.", 
            "dur": "2.546", 
            "start": "201.897"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A few decades ago, many scientists believed", 
            "dur": "2.458", 
            "start": "204.443"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that this could actually be possible.", 
            "dur": "2.258", 
            "start": "206.901"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Today, observations have shown", 
            "dur": "1.461", 
            "start": "209.159"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that there is no significant amount of antimatter", 
            "dur": "2.418", 
            "start": "210.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "anywhere in the visible universe,", 
            "dur": "2.337", 
            "start": "213.038"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is weird because, like we said before,", 
            "dur": "2.051", 
            "start": "215.375"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there should be just as much antimatter", 
            "dur": "2.144", 
            "start": "217.426"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as there is matter in the universe.", 
            "dur": "2.392", 
            "start": "219.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Since antiparticles and particles", 
            "dur": "2.081", 
            "start": "221.962"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "should exist in equal numbers,", 
            "dur": "3.177", 
            "start": "224.043"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this missing antimatter?", 
            "dur": "1.757", 
            "start": "227.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now that is a real mystery.", 
            "dur": "2.612", 
            "start": "228.977"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To understand what might be happening,", 
            "dur": "1.541", 
            "start": "231.589"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we must go back to the Big Bang.", 
            "dur": "2.379", 
            "start": "233.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the instant the universe was created,", 
            "dur": "2.279", 
            "start": "235.509"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a huge amount of energy was transformed into mass,", 
            "dur": "3.949", 
            "start": "237.788"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and our initial universe contained", 
            "dur": "2.197", 
            "start": "241.737"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "equal amounts of matter and antimatter.", 
            "dur": "2.629", 
            "start": "243.934"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But just a second later,", 
            "dur": "1.583", 
            "start": "246.563"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "most matter and all of the antimatter", 
            "dur": "2.876", 
            "start": "248.146"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "had destroyed one another,", 
            "dur": "1.742", 
            "start": "251.022"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "producing an enormous amount of radiation", 
            "dur": "3.068", 
            "start": "252.764"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that can still be observed today.", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "255.832"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just about 100 millionths", 
            "dur": "2.368", 
            "start": "258.082"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the original amount of matter stuck around", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "260.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and no antimatter whatsoever.", 
            "dur": "2.666", 
            "start": "263.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Now, wait!&quot; you might say,", 
            "dur": "2.005", 
            "start": "265.786"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Why did all the antimatter disappear", 
            "dur": "2.583", 
            "start": "267.791"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and only matter was left?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.339", 
            "start": "270.374"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It seems that we were somehow lucky", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "272.713"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that a tiny asymmetry exists", 
            "dur": "2.382", 
            "start": "275.003"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "between matter and antimatter.", 
            "dur": "1.876", 
            "start": "277.385"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Otherwise, there would be no particles at all", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "279.261"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "anywhere in the universe", 
            "dur": "1.508", 
            "start": "281.841"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and also no human beings.", 
            "dur": "2.089", 
            "start": "283.349"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But what causes this asymmetry?", 
            "dur": "2.178", 
            "start": "285.438"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Experiments at CERN are trying to find out the reason", 
            "dur": "2.752", 
            "start": "287.616"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "why something exists", 
            "dur": "2.151", 
            "start": "290.368"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and why we don&#39;t live in a universe", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "292.519"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "filled with radiation only?", 
            "dur": "2.014", 
            "start": "294.639"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, so far, we just don&#39;t know the answer.", 
            "dur": "3.637", 
            "start": "296.653"
        }
    ], 
